Seasonal temperature changes in Arctic Alaska

1 Overview

This project seeks to answer the following research question:

Is Arctic shrubification controlled by winter or summer temperatures?

1.1 Research Questions:

This analysis is composed of four subquestions:

  1. How has the mean July temperature of Arctic Alaska changed over the past 39 years (1979-2018)?

  2. How has the mean January temperature of Arctic Alaska changed over the past 39 years?

  3. Have winter or summer temperatures changed more over the study period?

  4. Are there any observable patterns of shrub expansion that can be explained by changes in winter or summer temperatures?

1.2 Rationale:

  • High latitude regions are projected to warm at twice the rate of the global average (IPCC 2013)
  • Permafrost thaw releases greenhouse gases & contributes to more warming
  • Shrubs are expanding & contribute to climate feedback cycles
    • Taller shrubs store more carbon - less carbon in atmosphere
    • Taller shrubs trap snow - soil is warmer during winter - increases permafrost thaw
  • In order to model changes in vegetation and climate we need a thorough understanding of ecosystem processes
  • However, the controls on shrub expansion are not well understood

1.3 Data:

NCEP North American Regional Reanalysis (NARR) monthly temperature at 2m height (air.2m.mon.mean)

Source: NCEP Reanalysis data provided by the NOAA/OAR/ESRL PSD, Boulder, Colorado, USA, from their Web site at https://www.esrl.noaa.gov/psd/

1.4 Methodology:

  • Load NetCDF4 File
  • Load shapefile of Arctic Alaska
  • Extract data from region of interest
  • Index plot of January temperatures
  • Index plot of July temperatures
  • Box plot of mean temperature change
  • Load shapefile of shrub expansion
  • Heatmap of seasonal temperature changes
  • Evaluate pattern of climatic and vegetation change

1.5 Current road-blocks & troubleshooting efforts:

  • Extracting data from ncdf based upon shapefile extent
  • Analyzing regional change in temperature over time (need extracted data)
  • Overlaying shapefile-derived map boundaries on plots (& maps libarary doesnt have AK map)
  • Loading geotiff file

2 Load NetCDF4 File

library(sf) 
library(ncdf4)
library(raster)
library(rasterVis)
library(RColorBrewer)

# set path and filename
ncpath <- "/Users/Ori/Documents/REarthSysSci/"
ncname <- "air.2m.mon.mean"  
ncfname <- paste(ncpath, ncname, ".nc", sep="")
dname <- "air"  # note: tmp means temperature (not temporary)

# open a netCDF file
ncin <- nc_open(ncfname)
lon <- ncvar_get(ncin,"lon")
nlon <- dim(lon)
lat <- ncvar_get(ncin,"lat")
nlat <- dim(lat)

# get time
time <- ncvar_get(ncin,"time")
tunits <- ncatt_get(ncin,"time","units")
nt <- dim(time)

# get temperature
tmp_array <- ncvar_get(ncin,dname)
dlname <- ncatt_get(ncin,dname,"long_name")
dunits <- ncatt_get(ncin,dname,"units")
fillvalue <- ncatt_get(ncin,dname,"_FillValue")

# get global attributes
title <- ncatt_get(ncin,0,"title")
institution <- ncatt_get(ncin,0,"institution")
datasource <- ncatt_get(ncin,0,"source")
references <- ncatt_get(ncin,0,"references")
history <- ncatt_get(ncin,0,"history")
Conventions <- ncatt_get(ncin,0,"Conventions")

# get geographic coordinate information 
grid_mapping_name <- ncatt_get(ncin, "Lambert_Conformal", "grid_mappping_name")
standard_parallel <- ncatt_get(ncin, "Lambert_Conformal", "standard_parallel")
longitude_of_central_meridian <- ncatt_get(ncin, "Lambert_Conformal", "longitude_of_central_meridian")
latitude_of_projection_origin <- ncatt_get(ncin, "Lambert_Conformal", "latitude_of_projection_origin")
false_easting <- ncatt_get(ncin, "Lambert_Conformal", "false_easting")
false_northing <- ncatt_get(ncin, "Lambert_Conformal", "false_northing")

#nc_close(ncin)

# load some packages
library(chron)
library(lattice)
library(RColorBrewer)
library(ggplot2)
library(rasterVis)
library(maptools)
library(maps)

# convert time -- split the time units string into fields
tustr <- strsplit(tunits$value, " ")
time_corr <- as.POSIXct(unlist(tustr)[3],tz = "UTC")+as.difftime(time,units="hours")

# replace netCDF fill values with NA's
tmp_array[tmp_array==fillvalue$value] <- NA

8 Extract regional data from ncdf

tmp_brick <- brick(tmp_array, xmn=min(lon), xmx=max(lon), ymn=min(lat), ymx=max(lat), crs=CRS("+proj=lcc +lat_1=20 +lat_2=60 +lat_0=40 +lon_0=-96 +x_0=0 +y_0=0 +ellps=GRS80 +datum=NAD83 +units=m +no_defs"))

arctic_data <- extract(tmp_brick, SpatialPoints(arctic_outline), method='simple')

arctic_df <- data.frame(tmp_array=time(arctic_data))
